image.characterName: モブ HK_筋肉おやじ（大）01-1

parameters: ストーリー　セレナ売ります
...\n< Serena>

Now, adventurer, there's something I
want to ask you.\n< Man>

Do you understand what you've done...
what exactly you're responsible for?\n< Man>
I did the right thing.\n< Serena>
...I see.\n< Man>

An unsuitable person was given an
unsuitable job.\n< Man>

Accidents are precisely things that
happen in such cases.\n< Man>
A major loss. A significant loss indeed.\n< Man>

The total debt carried by the women who
fled is 58,000 S.\n< Man>

The opportunity loss caused by this
commotion is roughly 300,000 S.\n< Man>

Furthermore, you have incurred a penalty
of 800,000 S for breaching the first,
third, and fourth regulations.\n< Man>

That brings the total to 1,103,800 S.
Adding the future losses this incident
will cause to the guild, your debt to
the guild is now 2,000,000 S.\n< Man>
Any objections?\n< Man>
None.\n< Serena>
Oh?\n< Man>

I did what I had to do. I have nothing
to be ashamed of.\n< Serena>

You all should do what you must as well.
That would be fair, wouldn't it?\n< Serena>

...You have a way to repay such an
amount personally?\n< Man>
Not at the moment, unfortunately.\n< Serena>

Of course, if I were allowed to continue
as an adventurer, I'm confident that I
would eventually be able to repay it.\n< Serena>

Naturally, that option is out of the
question.\n< Man>

But if that's the case, we have no
choice but to lay our hands on your
body, which is the only capital you
possess.\n< Man>
The problem is how to monetize it.\n< Man>
Chancellor.\n< Subordinate>
I understand.\n< Man>

...Adventurer Serena. As a measure
against the losses incurred this time,
we hereby strip you of your right to be
your own master.\n< Man>

From today onwards, you will be
designated as a city slave, and we will
auction off the right to be your master
in order to compensate for the losses.\n< Man>

Me, a slave? The ownership of slaves
within the kingdom is supposed to be
forbidden by church law.\n< Serena>

What you will become is a 'city slave.'
Within the city limits, your freedom of
movement, action, and private property
ownership will be restricted.\n< Man>

This is not the slavery prohibited by
the church. The words may sound
similar... oh, I've just realized. This
is not good... it's a misleading
expression.\n< Man>

It may well be corrected in time. But
for now, you have become what is known
as a city slave.\n< Man>
...Despicable people.\n< Serena>

Very well. Do as you like with me as a
slave or at auction.\n< Serena>

But no matter what title I bear, I am
still myself. Make sure you don't
mistake a wolf for a dog just because of
its collar.\n< Serena>

A wise wolf would be content with a
dog's collar if it knew things could get
much worse.\n< Man>
Take her away.\n< Man>
Yes sir!\n< Subordinate>
